{
  "text": "In the current study, we showed that linseed-enriched diet up-regulated the expression of genes (SLC20A1, TRAF3IP2, TP53INP1, TNFRSF12A, TLR9 and BIRC2) which involved in I\u03baB inhibition in porcine skeletal muscle, and might lead to decrease NF-\u03baB activation (Table 5 ). Recent studies indicated that activation of NF-\u03baB is inhibited by n-3 PUFAs in lymphomonocyte [CITATION_1] , and the decreased IKK activation is likely to contribute to the suppressed NF-\u03baB activation [CITATION_2] . Our results provided an alternative explanation why n-3 PUFAs could suppress NF-\u03baB activation.",
  "correct_citation": {
